docs {
  # Conversation History Endpoint
  
  Retrieves message history for a specific conversation/channel.
  
  ## Path Parameters
  - `channelId`: The ID of the channel to get history for (e.g., C1234567890)
  
  ## Query Parameters
  - `cursor` (optional): Pagination cursor
  - `latest` (optional): End of time range of messages to include in results
  - `oldest` (optional): Start of time range of messages to include in results  
  - `inclusive` (optional): Include messages with latest or oldest timestamp
  - `limit` (optional): Maximum number of messages to return (default: 100)
  
  ## Response
  - Complex message history data structure
  - Returns 500 error if Slack API is not accessible
}
